cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a neural network model for recognizing handwritten mathematical expressions, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques for analyzing the two-dimensional structure of expressions and natural language processing (NLP) techniques for identifying different mathematical symbols. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The model also involves deep learning techniques, which fall under cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also discusses the use of visualization to show the recognition process, which could fall under cs.CL. Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance on public datasets, which could fall under cs.IR.
